\n<Roselitte>"Let's have Ameria look at our injuries before we move on."

\n<Ameria>"The Gluttonous Grimoire, Begierde... I wonder if such a
thing really exists."

\n<Roselitte>"I don't know... But the power that Deoruk showed us was
real. Since there's nothing else that can explain it, it
seems we have no choice but to believe in it for now."

\n<Roselitte>"I didn't get the impression that the succubus was lying.
Well, she might just be a good actress."
\n<Ameria>"...Roselitte-san. Lyric is a good girl, right...?"

\n<Roselitte>"Her body was brought here by your sister, wasn't it? Didn't
you ask for more details?"

\n<Ameria>"Yes. Before we could have a proper talk, she said she had
'something to do' and left immediately."

\n<Ameria>"...But you know, there's one thing that's been bothering
me."

\n<Ameria>"When my sister brought Lyric here, she emphasized strongly
not to let her out of the church. She said it's because
there are people after Lyric."

\n<Roselitte>"...Deoruk and his group were plotting your kidnapping and
the murder of the succubus. Could there be a connection?"

\n<Ameria>"Maybe... Did my sister know that we were being targeted by
thieves?"

\n<Roselitte>"It's a bit troubling... but let's investigate this matter
once things have settled down. Is that alright with you?"

\n<Ameria>"If you need me again, just call. Don't push yourself too
hard until then, okay?"

\n<Ameria>"Show me your injury, Roselitte-san. You overdid it in the
cave, so we need to take a proper look."

\n<Roselitte>"No, it's just that right now I'm a little... Please,
later."
\n<Ameria>"I see... Alright. But don't overdo it, okay?"

\n<Roselitte>"...So? What did you mean by 'I'll let you win' that you
mentioned earlier? Do tell."
\n<Roselitte>"Hurry up. We don't have time to dawdle."
\n<Lyric>"...Before that, there's something I want to say."

\n<Lyric>"E-earlier... I mean... when I raised my hand... I-I was
wrong."

\n<Roselitte>"--What...? What are you getting at? A monster apologizing
to a human is unheard of."

\n<Lyric>"...Earlier, Ameria told me. Even if someone says something
unpleasant, don't raise your hand. Apologize first."

\n<Lyric>"Well, it's true that I'm a monster and you're a knight.
It's natural to be suspected, and it was rash of me to get
angry over just a little provocation."
Lyric bowed her head towards Roselitte.

\n<Lyric>"--That's it, it's over! Forget about this right away, you
stupid knight!"

\n<Lyric>"Got it? I only did it because Ameria told me to. Who would
willingly bow their head to a knight, idiot!"

\n<Lyric>"You ungrateful! Heartless human! Even though I saved you as
a favor to Ameria, why should I have to apologize!"

\n<Lyric>"And of course I'd get mad if you say something annoying!
You don't know anything about me! Idiot! Idioooot!!!"
\n<Roselitte>"Ah, no... just thinking how embarrassed you look."
\n<Roselitte>"...There really are some strange monsters out there."

\n<Roselitte>"Indeed, even if you are a monster, it would be rude not to
thank someone who helped you. Thank you, succubus."

\n<Lyric>"That's quite a rude way to start a conversation. But look,
there's an expert right in front of you. Ask them."

\n<Ameria>"Yes. Preservation magic was cast, and there was no pulse or
breath. The priest also examined you, so there's no
mistake."

\n<Lyric>"...Your sister, that Stella person, she really didn't say
anything? Like who saved me, or why she brought me here?"

\n<Ameria>"Yes... I'm sorry. My sister spoke with the priest for a bit
and then left immediately."

\n<Roselitte>"...It's hard to believe, but if Ameria says so, then you
must have truly been dead. What exactly happened?"

\n<Lyric>"Just like I said before. I tried to corrupt a certain
knight, but I failed and got beaten instead."

\n<Lyric>"...That guy did something terrible to me, and I had a wish
I desperately wanted to come true. If I had corrupted the
knight and satisfied Begi-Ade's hunger, my wish was supposed
to be granted."

\n<Lyric>"Well, thinking about it now, even if I had succeeded in
corrupting him, I'm not sure if that guy would have really
granted my wish."

\n<Lyric>"...I probably would have failed, I think. I have this
feeling that Begi-Ade was just using me to consume that
knight's lust... definitely."
\n<Ameria>"...What was the wish you wanted to come true, Lyric?"
Roselitte and Ameria nodded at the same time.

\n<Roselitte>"The Desire-Eater Grimoire, Begi-Ade... A magical book that
consumes desires written within it and uses them as
nourishment to grant its owner's wishes..."
\n<Roselitte>"I can hardly believe such a thing exists. It's incredible."
\n<Ameria>"...Hey, Lyric. Can I ask you something?"

\n<Ameria>"Lyric, you've been feeding Begi-Ade with lust, right? Why
is that? Aren't other desires like hunger or the need for
sleep enough?"

\n<Lyric>"Of course they're not enough. I fed it lust because that's
what Begi-Ade asked for... Hmm, let me think..."
\n<Lyric>"...There are two reasons why feeding it lust is better."
With that said, Lyric raised one finger.

\n<Lyric>"I am serious! I was asked to feed it lust. That's the best
proof there is."

\n<Lyric>"We choose our favorite foods like meat or fish to eat,
right? Desires are the same... probably."
\n<Roselitte>"Begi-Ade likes lust... What a complex feeling this is."

\n<Lyric>"Remember what I said earlier? 'The quality and quantity of
the desire fed to Begi-Ade determines the limits of the wish
it can grant.' The fact that it likes lust speaks to the
quality."
With that said, Lyric raised two fingers.

\n<Lyric>"And the second reason is about quantity. Consuming lust is
efficient."

\n<Lyric>"For example, with hunger, once you're full you don't want
to eat anymore. With the need for sleep, after a good rest
you don't feel like sleeping again right away."

\n<Lyric>"But what about sexual desire... lust? What do you think?...
Ameria, after you masturbate, don't you sometimes think
'just a little more...' and do it again?"
\n<Ameria>"N-no...! That's not something I've ever done!"

\n<Lyric>"Liar! You've definitely thought 'It's not enough! Just one
more time!' after masturbating at least once... right,
Knight-sama?"

\n<Lyric>"Lust is a desire that grows the more it's satisfied, a
strong desire. That's why it makes sense to consume it."

\n<Lyric>"The reason Begi-Ade chose me as its owner is surely because
I'm an incubus. I'm good at arousing people, so there
couldn't be a more convenient owner for Begi-Ade, right?"

\n<Ameria>"So, in other words, Begi-Ade prefers lust, and lust can
efficiently become its nourishment, which it uses to grant
the owner's wishes... right?"

\n<Ameria>"...And, 'by writing memories in the book, we can feed it
desires.'... right?"

\n<Roselitte>"...Now then, let's get to the main point. What do you mean
by 'I'll let you win'? Do you have a plan to defeat Deorc?"

\n<Lyric>"Yeah. Well, it's not like I'm saying we can definitely
win."

\n<Lyric>"...Right now, we're far from being in perfect condition.
Knight-sama is recovering from injuries. Ameria isn't used
to fighting... and even I can't use magic as I'd like to
right now."

Lyric looked down at her own palm and clenched it several
times as if to check something.
\n<Lyric>"Actually, I can use it too. The art of monster taming."

\n<Lyric>"No, it's impossible. Actually, because I died once, I
hardly have any magical power left now."

\n<Lyric>"Monster taming requires a vast amount of magical power, and
right now I can barely use any other spells properly
either."

\n<Lyric>"Besides, since waking up, something's been off. Even when I
try to use spells, 'I don't feel like I can.' No... 'I don't
know how to use them,' maybe..."

\n<Lyric>"Anyway, right now I'm just like you, not in a state where I
can fight properly. It would be difficult for us to defeat
Deorc as we are now."

\n<Roselitte>"...So far from helping us win, you're not even combat-
ready."
Saying that, Lyric placed her hand on her chest.

\n<Lyric>"It's true that I don't have the power to fight right now.
But I have a special ability that's separate from that."
\n<Lyric>"Yes. I can transfer or lend my power to someone else."

\n<Roselitte>"...Who exactly are you? Succubi are known to be high-
ranking demons, but not all of them have that ability, do
they?"

\n<Lyric>"Well, that's why. If my magical power... that is, my mana
returns to normal, then I can use this ability to make you
stronger."

\n<Roselitte>"...So you're saying if you regain your lost magical power
and gain strength, you can transfer that power to me,
allowing me to level up faster... is that it?"
\n<Lyric>"Exactly. You catch on quick; that helps."

\n<Lyric>"That's why I want you to help me recover my magical power
while we travel. Then not only will I become stronger, but
you yourself will also become stronger... How about it? It's
not a bad deal, right?"
\n<Roselitte>"...Understood. So what exactly do you want me to do?"
\n<Lyric>"Nfufu. Don't be so tense; it's not that kind of talk."
\n<Lyric>"Now, here's a question for you! Ta-dah!♪"
\n<Lyric>"How do succubi usually acquire magical power?♪"
\n<Roselitte>"...Ah, I have a bad feeling about this..."

\n<Lyric>"Ding-dong! Surely the correct answer! Succubi convert the
vital energy obtained from sexual activities into magical
power, which they can use to strengthen themselves."
\n<Lyric>"So, I want you to have sex with me."
\n<Roselitte>"Sigh!? Why on earth would that lead to this!"
\n<Lyric>"Eh, don't be so reluctant. It won't hurt, you know."

\n<Roselitte>"It's not about that... If you can gain power through sexual
activities, then I'm not needed. Go ahead and do as you
please with the demons around here."

\n<Lyric>"That's a harsh way to put it. Sex is a more sacred thing,
you know?"
\n<Roselitte>"I don't want to hear that from a succubus."

\n<Lyric>"Well, well. But you see, there's a good reason for having
sex with you. It's the most efficient method."

\n<Lyric>"Succubi live off the vital energy of humans. So the more
vital energy I can get, the stronger my power becomes."

\n<Lyric>"However, this vital energy isn't something only succubi can
obtain. It's generated by anyone who engages in sexual
activities, and even you, without realizing it, harbor vital
energy within your body."

\n<Lyric>"What makes succubi special is that we can freely 'absorb'
that vital energy and use it as nourishment."

\n<Lyric>"So, given that your fighting power has weakened, you're
likely to be attacked by many men from now on, right?"

\n<Lyric>"Then, the more you're attacked, the more vital energy will
be generated within you. I plan to become stronger by having
you transfer that energy to me."

\n<Lyric>"Vital energy grows like a snowball when one is aroused. The
more it's satisfied, the bigger it gets. The bigger it
becomes, the more it overflows. That's why it's more
efficient to receive vital energy from just you."
\n<Roselitte>"Desire... No, it sounds like lust to me."

\n<Lyric>"You just need to continue fighting as usual and regain your
original strength. I'll also regain my power through
experience in the process."

\n<Lyric>"But if you 'unfortunately' acquire vital energy in the
process, I want you to release it to me. That way, both you
and I can become stronger more efficiently."

\n<Roselitte>"...So basically, if I'm attacked by men and then engage in
sexual activities with you, I can level up faster... is that
it?"
\n<Lyric>"See?♪ It's not such a bad deal, right?"

\n<Roselitte>"'See?' is not the point! Even if it's for the sake of
getting stronger, I couldn't possibly do such a thing!"

\n<Lyric>"You're in a hurry to proceed, right? Given the situation,
you can't afford to be picky. And--"
Lyric gently placed a finger on her lips.

\n<Lyric>"A kiss is also a legitimate form of sexual activity. I find
sex more enjoyable but actually, just kissing is enough to
acquire vital energy."

\n<Lyric>"If you find yourself in an erotic situation, just kiss me.
Then both you and I will become stronger... So, what do you
say? This should be easy, right?"

\n<Lyric>"Alright, it's a deal! Don't worry. You'll get used to it
soon enough."
\n<Roselitte>"...I feel like I've been completely taken for a ride."

\n<Tutorial>Roselitte can acquire 'Special Experience Points' by
engaging in lewd acts during battles or events in addition
to achieving victory in combat.

\n<Tutorial>Special Experience Points can be converted into regular
experience points by talking to Lyric--kissing her--which
allows for leveling up. At the same time, Lyric will also
grow stronger.

\n<Tutorial>You can check your Special Experience Points from the menu
screen. Make sure they have accumulated before talking to
Lyric.

\n<Tutorial>To kiss, you can either talk to Lyric directly at a resting
point or use the item "Call Lyric". You can call her with a
shortcut by pressing the C key (default), so make sure to
use it actively.

\n<Tutorial>Note that the special shortcut keys are only for calling
Lyric with the C key (default) and for calling up the save
menu with the S key (default).

\n<Tutorial>This concludes the tutorial on "Special Experience Points".
If you want to see the explanation again, please check it
from the items menu.
